    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missing mandatory SCI fields and null pointer dereference in SL procedures\n\n### Summary\nThe sidelink procedures had two critical issues:\n1. Missing initialization of mandatory fixed fields in SCI format 1A structure leading to undefined values in outgoing signaling\n2. Null pointer dereference in resource pool handling functions when called with invalid parameters\n\nThese issues caused incorrect SCI message generation and potential crashes during sidelink operation.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/nr_ue_procedures_sl.c`: \n  * Added null pointer checks in `sl_get_subchannel_size()` and `sl_get_num_subch()` functions\n  * Initialized fixed SCI fields (priority, mcs, etc.) with default values in `sl_determine_sci_1a_len()`\n  * Fixed formatting issues in SL MAC PDU processing\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Configure UE with sidelink resource pool\n2. Trigger SCI format 1A generation with uninitialized fields\n3. Observe garbage values in priority/mcs fields of outgoing SCI\n4. Call `sl_get_num_subch()` with NULL resource pool pointer\n5. Observe segmentation fault\n\nThe fix ensures all mandatory SCI fields are properly initialized and prevents crashes from invalid resource pool parameters.\n"
}